    "body": "@beether how do you expect it to work? `sha3(0)` should be the same as `sha3(uint8(0))`, should be the same as\r\n```\r\nuint 8 x = 0;\r\nsha3(x);\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, `sha3(uint(0))` is a different value which should be equal to `uint x = 0; sha3(x);`.",
